📈 Business Recommendations
Recommendation 1

Focus future marketing campaigns on high-income and high-spending customers, as they have the highest likelihood of responding.

Recommendation 2

Develop personalized marketing campaigns instead of sending identical promotions to all customers.

Recommendation 3

Introduce loyalty programs to retain high-value customers and encourage repeat purchases.

Recommendation 4

Offer discounts and promotional coupons to low-spending customers to increase engagement.

Recommendation 5

Launch re-engagement campaigns for customers with high recency to encourage them to return.

Recommendation 6

Use customer segmentation based on Income, Total Spend, Purchase Frequency, and Recency for more effective marketing.

🏁 Final Conclusion

The analysis shows that Income and Total Spending are the strongest indicators of customer response to marketing campaigns. Customers with higher income and spending are more likely to accept marketing offers, while age has only a limited impact. Segmenting customers based on income, spending behavior, purchase frequency, and recency can help the company design personalized campaigns, improve customer engagement, increase campaign effectiveness, and maximize overall revenue.